## GTM Applications

This tool creates "Provokes" for sales conversations:

**Template:**
> "[Utility Name] customers pay [X]% more than the national average ([$rate]/kWh vs [$national_avg]/kWh) while [Y]% of your service territory lives below the poverty line. How are you identifying and supporting these vulnerable customers?"

**Example from #1 result:**
> "Alaska Village Electric Coop customers pay 211% more than the national average ($0.70/kWh vs $0.22/kWh) while 10.2% of your service territory lives below the poverty line. These remote communities face a perfect storm of energy burden."

---

## Data Sources

### EIA Form 861
- **Publisher:** U.S. Energy Information Administration
- **URL:** https://www.eia.gov/electricity/data/eia861/
- **Update Frequency:** Annual

### Census ACS Table S1701
- **Publisher:** U.S. Census Bureau
- **Table:** Poverty Status in the Past 12 Months
- **Variable:** S1701_C03_001E (Percent below poverty level)
- **URL:** https://data.census.gov/table/ACSST5Y2023.S1701

---

## Quick Reference

```bash
# Standard run
python3 affordability_index.v3.py

# Fast run (state-level only)
python3 affordability_index.v3.py --no-county

# Top 20 utilities
python3 affordability_index.v3.py --top 20

# Full customization
python3 affordability_index.v3.py \
  --top 20 \
  --no-county \
  --output-dir final_results
```

**Output:** Always in `[output-dir]/utility_affordability_index_top10.csv`

